vintage.name: Vintage But New Peyote Bird Designs Watch, Necklace, Bracelet
vintage.description: I had a southwest store in Sonoma County years ago and closed it in 1995. I personally went to New Mexico in the 1980s and early 1990s and worked with the Native American Indians and southwest artisans for this Peyote Bird Designs vintage but new hand beaded artisan watch bracelet, necklace and 5 strand bracelet.  Peyote Bird Designs is out of Santa Fe, New Mexico.  Beautiful Peyote Bird watch has a hand crafted band signed by Don Lucas. The watch and necklace also has Peyote Bird Designs Hallmark stamped on the back of watch and on a charm on the necklace showing that it is a Peyote Bird Designs original.The vintage but new watch has been in storage since 1995 and has never been worn and is still in it's original box as you can see in the photos in this ad.   So it is vintage but new.  I also have a beautifully handcrafted matching necklace and bracelet.  These can be bought as a set or purchased separately.  There is a discount if more than one item is purchased. The Peyote Bird watch has a triple strand beaded band with genuine Amethyst and Onyx and other types of beads, one with small heart, star and flower sterling silver charms signed Don Lucas.   Watch and band components, charms etc are sterling silver.   The chain at one end makes the watch size adjustable and has a tiny Peyote Bird charm marked sterling, the other end has a hook to loop through the chain to fasten the band.   The third item is a Peyote Bird Designs beaded bracelet with black, white and silver with some purple very old beads has an African theme with an elephant, lion, hippo and zebra sterling silver charms.  The clasp is a authentic Indian head nickel.  Bracelet is vintage but new.  Never worn.The watch currently needs a battery that I can take care of once the watch is sold.   The watch and band are very sturdy and unique.  The band has hand tooled sterling silver, multi semi precious stones plus two charms have Onyx stones mounted in them as well as the stem for winding the watch also has Onyx. The watch face is 1 1/8 wide including stem. This western charm watch bracelets length is about 7 but can be made larger by using the additional chain links.  The watch band is a standout to layer with your Peyote Bird beaded bracelet, jewel tone or silver bracelets.   Made by Don Lucas and sold by Sundance in the 1980's and 1990's, it is a stunner. Hallmark stamped on back of watch.  Quartz Timepiece.  The watch will come in the original box.  Consider this for the one who loves designer signed vintage southwestern jewelry.PRICE CHARM WATCH:     $399PRICE MATCHING NECKLACE:    $125PRICE MATCHING BEADED AFRICAN THEME BRACELET:  $200DISCOUNT FOR PURCHASING MORE THAN ONE PIECE OF SET IS 5% If interested call or text Rebecca at  . vintage.name: 5 Size 10 Approximately Vintage Handmade Navajo And Zuni Rings
vintage.description: I have vintage handmade Navajo and Zuni rings for sale.  I used to have a southwest retail store in the 1980's that focused on only Native American jewelry, rugs and pottery.  I closed this store in 1995.  The sterling silver rings in this ad I personally went to New Mexico to work with the Native American Indians, Navajo and Zuni to buy for my shop.  So these are rings that have been in storage since 1995 and never worn in all those years.  I have priced these items separately below.1). SOLD. This vintage ring has a round large piece of black Onyx with a design in the outer sterling silver that replicates the outline of the Pueblo homes of the Native American people. This is a heavy Navajo ring, weighs one ounce.   Approximately 10 1/2 size.   Price:  $450. SOLD2).  Amazing piece with so many different stone insets! This is a vintage Zuni, Native American sterling silver ring by the silversmith Geonard Jim.  Zuni are known for their inlaid jewelry.  The ring is stamped with the artist's name.  It is inlaid with so many stones in a beautiful pattern. Some of them are red jasper, black onyx, turquoise, deep blue lapis lazuli and malachite.   Zuni tribe consists of only around 20,000 strong, so pieces by the Zuni are very desirable. The silver is wide with a wing pattern on each side.   Size, approximately 10-1/2.  Price:  $4003). SOLD. This vintage sterling silver Navajo ring  had a large piece of birdseye or what's known as spiderweb turquoise, a term that describes turquoise made up of many small turquoise nuggets surrounded by a darker blue matrix.  There are only a handful of mines that produce Birdseye turquoise, namely Turquoise Mountain, Kingman and Morenci.  Turquoise Mountain closed in the late 1980s is located near the Kingman mine in northwestern Arizona.  The silver and turquoise piece on top of the ring measures 1-1/2 long and 1 wide.   Size approximately 10.  Price:  $200. SOLD4).  This vintage sterling silver ring is by the Zuni tribe and made from spiny oyster shell.  It's found in the Sea of Cortez , Baja California, Mexico.  Spiny Oyster began to be exported for jewelry making the Southwest in 1976.  The Zuni tribe is only around 20,000 strong, so jewelry pieces by the Zuni are very desirable.  Weighs 1/2 ounce.  Size is approximately  10 1/2.  Price:  $1505). This Zuni vintage sterling silver ring has a Sun Face inlaid in the center.  It's inlaid with turquoise, mother of pearl, red jasper, green malachite, onyx, deep blue lapis.  The Sun Face is an important cultural symbol of the Zuni people and represents the Sun Father, one of their three main kachinas or deities.  Practicing an agricultural lifestyle like the other Native American tribes, the Zuni had a keen understanding of the relationship between different crops and different seasons.  They recognized the crucial impact of the Sun on the agricultural output.  Size approximately10 1/2.  Price:  $220 If interested in any of these rings, please call or text Rebecca at  .
